sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_M45632
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: A device to sense Vitamin D3
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: A composite part to report the amount of vitamin D3 in the media. Sensing is based on the quenching of the expression of blue chromoprotein, with increase of the concentration of vitamin D3.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Anna Doloman
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Device is composed of various standard parts. See each part description for details.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: gfasPurple
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This chromoprotein from the coral Galaxea fascicularis, gfasPurple, naturally exhibits strong color when expressed.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Sabri Jamal
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: Synthesized and codon optimized for E coli by GenScript.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K364312
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: the vitamin D receptor (VDR) and also known as NR1I1 (nuclear receptor subfamily 1, group I, member 1), is a member of the nuclear receptor family of transcription factors. Upon activation by vitamin D, the VDR forms a heterodimer with the retinoid-X receptor and binds to hormone response elements on DNA resulting in expression or transrepression of specific geneproducts. In humans, the vitamin D receptor is encoded by the VDR gene. Hinge region: Thought to be a flexible domain that connects the DBD with the LBD. Influences intracellular trafficking and subcellular distribution.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Lior Malka
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Human VDR (of the nuclear hormone receptor superfamily)
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: The reconstruction of the DBD to the hinge region and LBD will be done with RFC 25.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0034
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Vinay S Mahajan, Voichita D. Marinescu, Brian Chow, Alexander D Wissner-Gross and Peter Carr IAP, 2003.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Varies from -6 to +1 region from original sequence to accomodate BioBricks suffix.

No secondary structures are formed in the given RBS region. Users should check for secondary structures induced in the RBS by upstream and downstream elements in the +50 to -50 region, as such structures will greatly affect the strength of the RBS. Contact info for this part: Brian Chow

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K784002
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This part is a T7 RNAP Terminator, which can also be used for the following RNAP: T3,N4,K1F,SP6.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Lior Levy
